<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=101229230433674></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f101229230433674><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=8&mid=101229230433674>RE: my Meele opinion</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=8&mid=101229230433674#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=106549><span id= >Master Kenidian</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>5 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Jan 29th 4:20 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>as a 45 druid, meleeing is completely pointless unless you are bored, solo and have an escape route or mana to destroy the mob.&nbsp;&nbsp;my rules i use when hunting in a group are; NEVER melee in a group if you are the main healer (duh)  no need to melee in a group if you are the secondary healer.  you should be medding to full mana during fights.  snare the mob after tanks have aggroed the mob.  damage shield one maybe 2 of them.  keep an eye on the nukers health cuz the cleric is going to be busy with the tanks.  watch for adds and root if no mezzer is in your group, or kite it around until tanks are ready to kill it. with all of this going on you will find you have no time to melee.  i only melee when i am with guildmates in a group and we are balanced and only for fun.  when with a group of strangers, you have a job to do and meleeing is not it.     <br>&nbsp;<br>Kenidian Hawkwind<br>45 Druid-Warden of Tunare<br>Xegony</td></tr>
